---
name: project-autopilot-manager
description: General-purpose Codex project bot for initializing persistent atlas docs, creating bounded multi-phase task runs, keeping blueprint/map files updated after code changes, and automating fresh-session execution for scans, cleanup, revamps, feature work, and full project enhancement. Use when Codex should manage a project end-to-end instead of relying on repeated manual prompt transfer.
---

# Project Autopilot Manager

## Purpose

Run large project tasks through durable docs and bounded fresh-session phases so Codex can keep working without rescanning the entire codebase every time.

## Core Guarantees

- Keep atlas docs current after code changes.
- Store project memory in files, not chat memory.
- Split large work into bounded phases.
- Generate fresh-session prompts automatically.
- Work across different local projects by changing the target project path.

