# Project Blueprint

Last refreshed: 2026-03-07 (Phase 1 - Refresh Atlas Docs, system-atlas run "'`20260307-154419-system-atlas`).

## Scope
- Target project: `/Users/macbook/Desktop/Huz`
- Scope level: `panel-fullstack`
- Surfaces mapped in this refresh:
  - `Huz-Backend` (Django 5 monolith)
  - `Huz-Web-Frontend` (public/user React app)
  - `Huz-Admin-Frontend` (super-admin + partner panel React app)
  - `Huz-Operator-Frontend` (operator React app)

## Architecture Overview
- Backend is a modular Django monolith exposing REST endpoints across six route groups: `/api/v1`, `/common`, `/partner`, `/bookings`, `/management`, `/chat`.
- Frontend surfaces are split by audience:
  - `Huz-Web-Frontend`: website discovery and user booking lifecycle.
  - `Huz-Admin-Frontend`: super-admin approvals and partner/admin panel flows.
  - `Huz-Operator-Frontend`: partner/operator operational dashboard flows.
- API contracts are currently anchored in FE-side API utility modules (`src/api/*` and `src/utility/*`) instead of a shared typed contract package.

## System Surfaces and Entrypoints
| Surface | Path | Entrypoint | Primary Responsibility |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Backend | `Huz-Backend` | `huz/urls.py`, `manage.py`, `huz/asgi.py`, `huz/wsgi.py` | API routing, auth/profile, package/booking workflows, admin approvals, reporting, chat |
| Web Frontend | `Huz-Web-Frontend` | `src/index.js` -> `src/App.js` -> `src/routes/AppRoutes.jsx` | Public package browsing, booking, payments, user settings |
| Admin Frontend | `Huz-Admin-Frontend` | `src/index.js` -> `src/App.js` | Super-admin operations and partner panel workflows |
| Operator Frontend | `Huz-Operator-Frontend` | `src/main.jsx` -> `src/App.jsx` -> `src/routes/index.jsx` | Operator dashboard, package management, booking operations |

## Critical Product Flows
1. Web user signup/login/profile setup:
- `Huz-Web-Frontend/src/api/AuthApi.js` calls `/common/is_user_exist/`, `/common/send_otp_sms/`, `/common/verify_otp/`, `/common/manage_user_account/`, and profile update endpoints.

2. Package discovery and booking (web):
- Listing/detail modules call `/partner/get_featured_packages/`, `/partner/get_package_short_detail_for_web/`, `/partner/get_package_detail_by_city_and_date/`, `/partner/get_package_detail_by_package_id_for_web/`.
- Booking lifecycle spans `/bookings/create_booking_view/`, `/bookings/check_passport_validity/`, `/bookings/pay_booking_amount_by_transaction_*`, `/bookings/raise_complaint_booking_wise/`, `/bookings/raise_a_request/` and `/api/v1/users/me/bookings/`.

3. Partner/operator onboarding and package lifecycle:
- Admin/Operator auth + company setup consume `/partner/partner_login/`, `/partner/create_partner_profile/`, `/partner/register_as_company/`, `/partner/update_partner_company_profile/`, `/partner/update_company_logo/`, `/partner/get_partner_profile/`.
- Package creation/management consume `/partner/enroll_package_*`, `/partner/get_package_*_by_partner_token/`, `/partner/change_huz_package_status/`, `/partner/get_partner_overall_package_statistics/`.

4. Booking operations and complaint handling (admin/operator):
- `/bookings/get_all_booking_detail_for_partner/`, `/bookings/get_booking_detail_by_booking_number/`, `/bookings/partner_action_for_booking/`, `/bookings/manage_booking_documents/`, `/bookings/manage_booking_airline_details/`, `/bookings/manage_booking_hotel_or_transport_details/`.
- Complaint and rating operations are shared across admin/operator dashboards.

5. Super-admin approvals and financial controls:
- `Huz-Admin-Frontend/src/utility/Super-Admin-Api.js` uses `/management/fetch_all_pending_companies/`, `/management/approved_or_reject_company/`, `/management/approve_booking_payment/`, `/management/transfer_partner_receive_able_payments/` and related review endpoints.

## Ownership Boundaries
- `common` app: end-user identity, OTP, profile/account primitives.
- `partners` app: partner auth/profile, package operations, partner wallet and website package listing endpoints.
- `booking` app: booking lifecycle, partner-side booking actions, complaints/reviews/requests, plus v1 booking endpoints.
- `management` app: super-admin approvals, transfers, KPI/report endpoints, hotel master catalog.
- `chat` app: user/partner inbox/message APIs and websocket routing.
- FE API ownership:
  - Web: `src/api/AuthApi.js`, `src/api/apiService.js`, `src/api/homepageApi.js`, `src/api/listingApi.js`, `src/api/packageDetailApi.js`
  - Admin: `src/utility/AuthApis.js`, `src/utility/Api.js`, `src/utility/Super-Admin-Api.js`
  - Operator: `src/api/authAPI.js`, `src/api/companyAPI.js`, `src/api/PackageAPI.js`, `src/api/BookingApi.js`, `src/api/DashboardApi.js`, `src/api/WalletApi.js`, `src/api/ReviewRatingAPI.js`, `src/api/complaintsAPI.js`

## Known Constraints and Contract Drift
- Backend endpoints discovered: `122`
- Backend endpoints connected from FE: `89`
- Backend endpoints with no FE consumer: `33` (largest unconsumed groups are `management` reports + full `chat` REST set)
- FE endpoint literals missing backend route: `10`
- Drift endpoints currently referenced by FE but missing in backend URL map include:
  - `/management/apis/custom/manage/packages/`
  - `/partner/enroll_transport_package/`
  - `/partner/change_transport_package_status/`
  - `/partner/get_transport_package_by_token/`
  - `/partner/update_transport_package_basic_detail/`
  - `/partner/update_transport_package_photo/`
  - `/partner/update_partner_avatar/`
  - `/partner/upload_hotel_photos/`
  - `/partner/company_documents/`
  - `/partner/manage_partner_withdraw_request/F{param}/` (malformed FE literal)

## Phase 1 Notes
- This phase refreshed atlas/report docs only. No target-project code was changed.
- Full backend API inventory and FE module mapping are documented in `docs/atlas/API_SURFACE.md`.
